File: Tshwane has been without a mayor and municipal manager after several failed attempts by the DA to elect a new mayor. JOHANNESBURG - The National Council of Provinces backs the decision to place Tshwane under administration. Gauteng Premier David Makhura decided to invoke section 139 of the constitution two weeks ago, following the collapse of several council meetings. READ: Tshwane placed under administration Tshwane has been without a mayor and municipal manager after several failed attempts by the DA to elect a new mayor. This as the ANC and EFF staged walk-outs and boycotted council sittings. The DA is challenging the decision in court next week.